        "message": "LU-19872 build: check /boot/ for kernel config\n\nOften, the kernel config will be installed in /boot/.\nThis is common with custom built RPMs. Update Lustre\nconfigure to check here as well.\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nSigned-off-by: Timothy Day <timday@amazon.com>\nChange-Id: I7f5624aa8483b95e361f703a0f747152512b9962\nReviewed-on: https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/63983\nReviewed-by: Arshad Hussain <arshad.hussain@aeoncomputing.com>\nReviewed-by: James Simmons <jsimmons@infradead.org>\nTested-by: jenkins <devops@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Andreas Dilger <adilger@thelustrecollective.com>\nTested-by: Maloo <maloo@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <green@whamcloud.com>\n"
